cast.overview: The story of British officer T.E. Lawrence's mission to aid the Arab tribes in their revolt against the Ottoman Empire during the First World War. Lawrence becomes a flamboyant, messianic figure in the cause of Arab unity but his psychological instability threatens to undermine his achievements.
cast.title: Lawrence of Arabia

details.biography: Mohamed El Habachi (1939, Casablanca - 22 November 2013 in Casablancs) was a Moroccan actor. He was widely considered to be one of the pioneers of cinema and theater in Morocco, and was known for his performances in many Moroccan films such as Mirage, Bamou, Blood Wedding and The Barber of the Poor Quarter.
details.name: Mohamed El Habachi
